SIMPLE: bursar
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bursar
<hw>Bur"sar</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>bursarius</ets>, fr. <ets>bursa</ets> purse. See <er>Burse</er>,
and cf. <er>Purser</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A treasurer, or cash
keeper; a purser; <as>as, the <ex>bursar</ex> of a college, or of a
monastery</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A student to whom a stipend or bursary is paid for
his complete or partial support.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bursarship</ent>⟦br⟧
